Audio to Report Automation — High-Level Flow

1. USER INPUT
   - User sends an audio file or voice message via Telegram
   - System extracts metadata: duration, format, file size

2. COST ESTIMATION
   - Duration is evaluated against a credit-based pricing model
   - User is notified of the estimated cost in credits

3. CREDIT VALIDATION
   - System checks if the user has sufficient credits
   - If insufficient, user is prompted to purchase a credit package
   - Payment is processed through a third-party payment gateway

4. AUDIO PROCESSING
   - Audio is sent to a speech-to-text API for transcription
   - The raw transcript is then processed by an AI model

5. FORMAT SELECTION
   - User chooses an output format:
     - Quick summary
     - Detailed notes
     - Meeting minutes
     - Conference analysis
     - Study notes
   - Custom formats can also be defined via HTML/CSS templates

6. DOCUMENT GENERATION
   - The structured content is injected into a document template
   - A PDF or Word file is generated

7. DELIVERY
   - The final document is sent back to the user via Telegram

ADDITIONAL FEATURES
   - Dynamic inline menus for navigation
   - Credit history and balance tracking
   - Custom format creator (upload your own templates)
   - Processing history
   - Observability and tracing for performance monitoring

PROCESSING STRATEGY
   - Short audio (<20 min): Direct processing
   - Medium audio (20-90 min): Chunked processing
   - Long audio (>90 min): Specialized processing pipeline